---
title: fahrieren.com — Reliable Lead Pipeline (design/lead-pipeline-2026-06-05)
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor Visitor as Visitor<br/>(browser)
    participant Form as ContactPage /<br/>NewsletterForm
    participant Hook as useContactForm /<br/>useNewsletter (hook)
    participant LeadSvc as LeadService
    participant AppCheck as Firebase App Check<br/>(reCAPTCHA Enterprise)
    participant Firestore as Firestore<br/>/contacts or /newsletter
    participant Rules as Firestore<br/>Security Rules
    participant CF as Cloud Function<br/>onNewContactLead<br/>(2nd gen)
    participant Admin as Admin<br/>LeadsPage

    note over Visitor,Admin: S1 — Hardened rules + LeadService (flag OFF: dev only)
    note over Visitor,Admin: S2 — Wired forms + App Check (flag ON: staging)

    Visitor->>Form: Fills name/email/phone/subject/message<br/>Checks consent checkbox
    Form->>Hook: handleSubmit(formData, consentAt)
    Hook->>Hook: Client-side validation<br/>(Yup schema: required fields, max lengths)
    alt Validation fails
        Hook-->>Form: Return error; show i18n toast (leads.submit_error)
        Form-->>Visitor: Inline field errors; no write
    else Validation passes
        Hook->>LeadSvc: submitContact(payload)<br/>{ name, email, phone, subject, message,<br/>  category, source, language, consentAt,<br/>  createdAt: serverTimestamp() }
        LeadSvc->>AppCheck: SDK auto-attaches App Check token<br/>(ReCaptchaEnterpriseProvider)
        AppCheck-->>LeadSvc: Token attached to request
        LeadSvc->>Firestore: addDoc(collection(db,'contacts'), payload)
        Firestore->>Rules: Evaluate isValidContactLead(request.resource.data)
        alt Rules reject (missing consentAt / wrong shape / oversized field)
            Rules-->>Firestore: DENIED
            Firestore-->>LeadSvc: FirebaseError permission-denied
            LeadSvc-->>Hook: { success: false, error: 'permission-denied' }
            Hook-->>Form: Show error toast (leads.submit_error)
            Form-->>Visitor: Error — no data lost (no document created)
        else Rules accept
            Rules-->>Firestore: ALLOWED
            Firestore-->>LeadSvc: DocumentReference (autoId)
            LeadSvc-->>Hook: { success: true, docId }
            Hook-->>Form: status = 'success'
            Form-->>Visitor: Success toast (leads.contact_success)<br/>Form cleared; button disabled 30 s

            note over Visitor,Admin: Lead is now durable in Firestore — source of truth

            note over CF,Admin: S3 — Cloud Function notification
            Firestore-->>CF: onDocumentCreated event<br/>(/contacts/{contactId})
            CF->>CF: Read event.data.data()<br/>Check notifiedAt (idempotency guard)
            alt notifiedAt already set (retry)
                CF->>CF: Exit immediately (no double-notify)
            else First invocation
                CF->>CF: Format summary (TR):<br/>name, email, phone, subject, category
                CF->>Firestore: updateDoc (Admin SDK, bypasses rules):<br/>notifiedAt = serverTimestamp()<br/>whatsappDeepLink = formatted URL
                CF->>CF: Log structured JSON to Cloud Functions log
                opt NOTIFY_EMAIL_TO secret is set
                    CF->>CF: Send HTML email via nodemailer (SMTP)
                end
            end
        end
    end

    note over Visitor,Admin: S4 — Admin view
    Admin->>Firestore: query('contacts', orderBy('createdAt','desc'), limit(50))<br/>[Auth: isAdmin() check via admins/{uid} doc]
    Firestore-->>Admin: Lead documents (newest first)
    Admin->>Admin: Display lead list with filters<br/>(status: new / followed-up, category)
    Admin->>Firestore: updateDoc(contactRef, { status: 'followed-up' })
    Admin->>Admin: CSV export (client-side)
    Admin->>Admin: Open WhatsApp deep-link per lead<br/>(pre-fills context in owner's WhatsApp)
